# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. However, for a project, it's often user-specific:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a windows machine, the lockfile might not be portable
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains exact versions, but can be/should be git-committed
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains exact versions, but can be/should be git-committed
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; project local packages directory (used by pdm)
__pypackages__/

